main event: A very bright, white, oval-shaped object was observed moving across the sky on June 9, 1959.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be 2000-3000 yards away and at an altitude of 10,000 feet.
The witness was unable to determine if the object was a balloon, aircraft, or astronomical object.
The witness provided a sketch showing the object's position and motion.
The witness was asked to estimate the size, speed, and distance of the object, but did not provide definitive estimates.
sighted object: a very bright, white, oval-shaped object
